                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="451007" author="JIRAUSER18433" created="Thu, 3 Apr 2025 18:46:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;freedesktop spec for Trash &lt;a href=&quot;https://specifications.freedesktop.org/trash-spec/latest/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://specifications.freedesktop.org/trash-spec/latest/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="450366" author="adilger" created="Sat, 29 Mar 2025 22:07:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since this feature potentially impacts user workloads, it should be possible to disable the virtual &quot;&lt;tt&gt;.Trash&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; directory lookup on a client, in case users have e.g. accessed the Lustre mountpoint via NFS re-export to a Mac or similar. The &quot;&lt;tt&gt;.Trash&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; directory should be &lt;b&gt;enabled&lt;/b&gt; by default, but have a parameter like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;llite.&amp;#42;.trash_dir_enable&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; that enables and disables the virtual directory lookup. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be preferable if this could be tuned on a per-client basis with an &quot;llite&quot; parameter, but if that is not practical then an &quot;mdd&quot; parameter would also be Ok. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
